# Publishing Guide

## Prerequisites
  - npm account with publish access
  - Run: npm login

## Versioning (semver)
  - patch (0.1.x): Bug fixes, template improvements
  - minor (0.x.0): New features (new layer options, new templates)
  - major (x.0.0): Breaking changes (CLI interface changes, incompatible config)

## Steps

  1. Update version in package.json
  2. npm run build
  3. npm pack                    # Inspect .tgz contents
  4. npm publish
  5. git tag v{version}
  6. git push --tags

## Testing before publish

  npm run build
  npm pack
  # Creates cc-optim-{version}.tgz

  cd /tmp && mkdir test-proj && cd test-proj && npm init -y
  npx /path/to/cc-optim-{version}.tgz

## GitHub Release

  1. Create release on GitHub matching the version tag (e.g., v0.1.0)
  2. Include changelog in release notes
  3. Optionally attach the .tgz as release asset
